From Stephan Amann Subject Re more on radiosity In article Xia Zhao writes In article you write Let's be I'm working on a radiosity package written in C I would like to make it public I'll announce it in the minute I finished That were the good The bad news It'll take another months at least to finish Are you using the traditional radiosity method progressive refinement or something else in your package My package is based on several articles about non standard radiosity and some unpublished The main articles are Cohen Chen Wallace Greenberg A Progressive Refinement Approach to fast Radiosity Image Generation Computer Graphics SIGGRAPH pp August Silion Puech A General Two Pass Method Integrating Specular and Diffuse Reflection Computer Graphics SIGGRAPH July If you need to project patches on the hemi cube surfaces what technique are you using Do you have hardware to facilitate the projection I do not use hemi I have no special hardware SUN SPARCstation In the meantime you may have a look at the file Radiosity located at What are the guest username and password for this ftp site Use anonymous as username and your e mail address as there are some other locations have a look at archie to get the nearest Hope that'll Yours Stephan Thanks Josephine Stephan Amann SIG Computer Graphics University of Berne Switzerland Tel Fax Projects Radiosity Raytracing Computer Graphics